text: (upbeat music)
- My name is Doris Tang.

My job title is software
development engineer.

My team is Internet of
Things RoboRunner at AWS.

My journey with Amazon
started when I was in college.
I found a job posting,

and I applied for a summer
internship at Amazon Robotics.

It was the greatest three
months I've ever had in my life.
I met so many amazing people,
and that and the culture drew me

to start working here full-time
when I got the call back.
The goal of Internet of Things RoboRunner
is to help facilitate the management

of heterogeneous fleets of
robots that run at warehouses.

And I've grown from a
software development intern
to now a software development engineer.
And I hope to continue my trajectory

up to potentially
principal engineer someday
here at this company.
When I first joined AWS, I was nervous

that I wouldn't be as good
as the software teams here,
but because of the availability of mentors

and the breadth of
knowledge that the teams
are so ready to share here,

no one's going to say
no to helping you out.
If someone is watching this video,

and they want to join AWS,
I would say, just go for it.

You have nothing to lose,
and you will learn so much.
(upbeat music)
